The paper deals with the problem of Compressed Sensing (CS) with side information, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of L1-L1 and L1-L2 minimization, which are optimization techniques commonly used in Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper provides geometrical interpretations, which is a common approach in Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
